Carnage/ Dinobot

*Carnage glanced at Cyber Claw as she trotted up to her and spoke, so, now 
the clone relied on her for info? Well, that was a first, she sighed and 
continued to walk towards the Maximal base's old location. She didn't know 
about real casualties but she had her memories.*

" Once we get to the Maximals they can tell you who died and who lived, 
however, I can say this: many perished thanks to Megatron's insane causes."

* Carnage sighed, she wished that she could tell Cyber Claw more but there 
was no time for that...not now. She looked around as they came to the area 
where the Axalon once stood, there was nothing left but a slid mark where 
the ship had slid and plummeted into the water below.
Carnage growled, there was nothing left...not here.
She knew that there had to be Maximals and she knew that the signatures that 
she was scanning were them...but probably not the same ones that she had 
once fought against.*

____________________________________________________________


* Dinobot glanced as Tavatron had come back into the room, munching on food 
cubes. He hadn't moved from the spot in front of the door, he had been 
thinking about that secret, if Tavatron knew it, if she did then if she 
would teach it to him, and if he would be willing to learn.
Dinobot growled as he brought his hand to his chest and looked across the 
bridge as his repair system kicked in, the green energy coil from his spark 
wrapping around his and repairing his hand.
He looked at it once it had been healed, whom ever had built this body had 
made it aquipped with almost everything he could possibly need.
(doesn't know that Megs made it.)
Dinobot closed the door of the room and walked across the bridge, he passed 
Tavatron and made his way to the doors of the Ark. The urge to be out of the 
base and out in the open was to strong to ignore, he had to get out and away 
from the confines of the ship.*
